page.title: 08Wild Life
page.content:
There is a beck running through Dunston. This is the home for a large number of Mallards and Aylesbury ducks. The farmland and woods around the villages are ideal areas for a large variety of wild life. Pheasants, rabbits, hares and partridges are common.Kestrels have been seen on Dunston Fen and Barn Owls and Little Owls have been seen near the main Lincoln road.
Potterhanwoth Wood is a good area for butterflies. There are many different kinds of butterfly.The ones easily found are the comma,brimstone, red admiral, painted lady, and purple hairstreak. The wood attracts butterfly enthusiasts from the local area. _
